##super
is used to access/call the parent class members

##this
is used to call the current class members
We can use this() in the constructor of the class. It will reduce the code rewriting.

##Exception in static areas
We can use both of them anywhere in a class except static areas(the static block or a static method). Any attempt to do so will lead to a
compile-time errors

##Abstract class
Even abstract classes has constructor.